caption: Great service, Great food.... I had a Great time there

Matisse has a great food, nice outdoor patio with heaters that was open through Covid; and most importantly the wait staff is fantastic. Alex is amazing, very attentive and helpful. People like him make this place truly special, I Haven’t seen that much kindness in a long time! I will be back! Thank you!!

My girlfriend and I were staying in the hotel next door so we decided to check this place out. The wait was a little long but this is due to them making it from scratch. I can honestly, whole heartedly, confidently, say that this is THE BEST, food I have ever eaten in my life, and i love food, i came out of my mother eating and i have stopped stuffing my face for the past 21 years, and this is the absolute best food i have ever, ever had. If you live within a 100 mile radius of this place i would advise you to stop reading my review, go get your car keys, hop in your car and speed as fast as you can to this place. If I was on death row and had one more meal to eat it would be the fish tacos from here. I had to pinch myself multiple times, but no, i was not dreaming, this is heaven, and it’s in Chicago. I don’t care what you do in your life, it’s your life. But dear god please, PLEASE, before you die. EAT. HERE.

A solid 5 for their burgers. Made from scratch, fresh, great flavor and high quality. One of my favorite new burger discoveries. The fries are good and fresh, but I’d like to see them with a bit more flavor difference to make them just as craveable as the burger. Yummy! Will definitely go into my regular takeout rotation.
Delicious food and cocktails, great service.

Loooooong wait for our food. The menu was decent, the calamari appetizer was delicious. Our server was working both the inside and outside tables, which was a big part of the delays in service.  I hope they improve at that.
This place is perfect! The food is great and the atmosphere is relaxing.  The perfect place to unwind after a busy day.
Great cocktails and a lovely patio.  Will definitely be back again.

Some of the best Mediterranean in the city. Food is always fresh, service is fast and atmosphere makes it’s a great date spot. Cocktails are all amazing especially for 12$ bucks.. Highly recommend the calamari & any of the salads. 10/10 would recommend.
Nice patio area, friendly staff
Great “people watching” spot on a busy corner across from Trader Joe’s. Food is great, the Bistro Steak sammy with horseradish aioli is unreal!

I would say this is best burger place in Chicago area.  Burgers are not cheap but very delicious.I would definitely come again to try out other burgers they have.Servers were very friendly and constantly stop by our table to check if needed anything else.I kind of hesitated to dine at this place since it seemed like bar.  Yes, it is bar and very noisy but OK to take kids during day time.

I went here earlier today for a quick bite with my boyfriend, since we only had about 30 minutes to grab food before an appointment. The waiter was very nice, and the food was great!! The menu has some very interesting but tasty entrees and sandwiches, and you have to get the garlic french fries!! Big plus is the outdoor seating as well.

We were walking around and got into this place without any information because it had a outside setting and we were so satisfied. I had a vegetarian burger and my friend had a port chop and they were delicious! I had sweet potatoes as a side and it was sweet, well cooked, and warm. The service was top notch as well!
I went last night to celebrate my husband's birthday and It was an amazing experience. Food was delicious and the staff and the owner were amazing.

This is my favorite neighborhood bar and hang out spot. They have a wide range of cocktails and beer, and during non-pandemic times they offer daily specials on certain drinks. The food is also delicious with enough options for my gluten and dairy sensitive friends. They currently have a nice outdoor set up with plenty of heat lamps and enough plastic walls to keep out most of the wind.
Lovely neighborhood joint! Great food and cocktails!
Awesome cocktails, wine, and appetizers!  Love the Artichoke Dip!  Staff & Bartender are super nice and friendly.  HIGHLY Recommend!
Excellent food and service. Reasonable prices. A neighborhood staple!
Their Moscow mules made with homemade ginger beer are fantastic!! Food was also delicious and such a comfortable atmosphere.

One of my favorite restaurants in the neighborhood! Everything I've had on the menu is delicious, but you can't go wrong with any of their hamburgers. The atmosphere inside is cozy but upbeat, a great place for Friday night drinks and dinner with a friend.
Jennifer our waitress and Alex the owner were amazing!!! Drinks sooooo good!!! And food!!! We will deffinately come back for date night!!! Thanks for the new experience!😊

Alex and his staff are amazing! This is the perfect Neighbord place when everyone make you feel welcome ! And the food it’s amazing!!! You will keep going back forever! I am a 10 year customer and will be a forever customer of this amazing place 💖🙏👍🏻
Very good Experience dining here,  Very Fresh food ,Great Quality.
Great service! Great manager!
I must say the quesadillas are some of the best I've had and I've had a whole lot! They're not overly done with the right amount of flavor and the chipotle aioli adds a nice kick!
Live the cocktail menu and the staff was super nice
Love this place. Really good food no matter what you choose on the menu. The owner is pretty much always there, super helpful and really nice! Outdoor sitting is available right now!

Always a pleasure and great experience at Matisse, from pleasant, profesional friendly staff and services to best food quality at great value. A place where I'll return with excitment and pleasure, me and my friends, never dissapointed. Kudos to all at Matisse! Is 6 stars available yet?

Superb meal here on Monday 16th March we were served by Jennifer a very wonderful human being. We were her last table before the two week closure of all restaurants to diners in Chicago. An emotional experience ! Local non-chain restaurants like Matisse are the best thing about the USA for tourists an I guess locals too, they MUST be supported and cherished otherwise America will loose so much. Thank you again Jennifer and I hope you and all the restaurant staff can find a way throught these difficult times. Wirh love from David and Sonja x
Nice drinks & good music. Great desserts, the drunken monkey was amazing. It can get a bit noisy though, because it is a small space.
Generous pours, good service. I didn't get food but it smelled delicious
Had the best burger here(beats Kuma's Corner) and service is exceptional

JUST EAT HERE. We've dined in and ordered out on many occasions, nothing beats the DELICIOUS FOOD,  HIP COZY/FUN ATMOSPHERE, CARING, FRIENDLY,  AND ATTENTIVE STAFF! I highly recommend ordering the Rogue Hazelnut Brown Ale with Sweet Precision Soft Collision Burger. The goat cheese just melts in your mouth. Hands down the best Steak Quesadilla I've ever had. Cuban Spiced Won-tons are just right(our 8-year-old devours them). YOU'D BE A FOOL NOT TO EAT HERE!
Very Fun Times Great Service
Had brunch.  Excellent bloody mary and had the spinach and beat salad.  So good and not too pricey.  $50 fed and watered two of us.
Everything about this place is awesome! The servers are very attentive, the food is amazing, and they hand make the ginger beer for the mules!! Definitely Top Notch!!!
We love Matisse. Great space, food is marvelous.
Had a blast. Awesome place.

Been there both times we stayed in the area and it was great both times. The food is exceptionally good and the service is quick and friendly. Overall, it's a really nice little place I'd encourage anyone in the area to try!

Loved the almond-encrusted salmon and the rosemary chicken my partner and I ordered. Nice wine list, extensive beer, cocktail, and whiskey lists. Also want to give two big thumbs up to our hostrss/waitress Christina, who treated us so well. We stopped by shortly after they opened, so it was perfect for conversation. Looking forward to stopping by another time later in the evening to enjoy the neighborhood vibe!
Good food.. Good drinks.. Good service.. Nuff said
Came here for a few late night drinks and decided to try the Baked Brie. It was delicious!! Good environment to catch up with some friends.

Great local.place with a dog friendly patio during the summer, and the inside is cozy and warm during the winter, including a small fireplace. I personally recommend the cucumber martini and either the black bean burger or mac and cheese.
Great food and cocktails. Top notch service!
I love their steak nachos...and very nice wine list
Great time! Mike made us some fine cocktails!
Nice neighborhood place. Dog friendly patio.
I've been here many times now and used to live near by. I love the look and feel.  Always a good time.
Good burgers and surf and turf
(Translated by Google) Super comfortable, great food and about 70 beers! Top  (Original) Super gemütlich, tolles Essen und ca. 70 Biere! Top
Cool atmosphere.  Awesome food.
Fantastic people,  place and Food.  Thanks fo taking good care of us.  We will be back.

Nice atmosphere, good burgers and good sweet potato fries. It was a bit expensive for what it was, a burger is like $15 before tip and tax. I got the South of the Border burger and it was pretty good, lots of meat and the sweet potato fries were nice and crunchy.

Food was decent along with a good beer selection. Pricing was a little on the high side for food I thought, but probably pretty on par for Chicago. The server was nice and attentive as well! Only complaint was they really doused my BBQ burger in BBQ sauce, so I picked it up and immediately had it drip on my pants. By the end, my plate and hands were kind of a mess. Overall good.
Cool place, good beer, good nachos, burgers, friendly crew!
Best food in town! Also, super friendly service!
Fun. Good staff and food.

This place has a nice patio area, craft beers, surprisingly unique and delicious foods and flourishes like homemade ginger beer. That being said, 90% of the people who I've spoken to frequent this bar for one very sexy reason.
Our favorite neighborhood spot! Delicious food and drinks and great service. The patio is really nice in the summer months.
Great food and great service!
One of the best and most affordable meals you can get in Chicago!

Best burgers in town. Home made ginger bear is the best in the world. The Moscow mule has become my nieuw favorite drink. As a starter the wontons are great, if you want a burger you should try the one with the flambayde pears one of the best burgers you will have. Amazing service Marissa and Cristina thank you so much for the great time when i come back to Chicago you are the first thing on my list.
Good burger. Good selection of beer. Polite waiters. Fast Service. Chill atmosphere.
This is a great find.  The team.goes out of there way to welcome neighborhood locals.   Great Drink and Beer selection.   Small patio.  Bugers and Chicken all fresh and great.
Great outdoor patio!
The staff is fantastic and the food is amazing.
Food with real quality ingredients.  This place has a good design. I see why this place has so many great reviews.
Mac and cheese with bacon was most excellent
Loved this place. Traveled to Chicago from Detroit and the food and lighting and atmosphere was just awesome. Made me feel very good and comfortable.

Amazing burgers and even better service!! Loved the atmosphere and my boyfriend and I had a wonderful dinner date. We had the best server (Marissa M.) and she took fantastic care of us!! We loved her and loved our food. The artichoke dip was a heavenly appetizer while we waited on our burgers. Great drinks too and a lovely outdoor patio to enjoy the sunshine.  Definitely recommend this restaurant!!!

Best hamburger! Very friendly place and very clean. I have met the owner, he is a very nice guy. He always tries to make the costumer feel comfortable. If you want to have drinks and food this is the right place to go.
Good food and folks.
Great food and a funny  bar tender
I was so full. Had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. I see why this place has a lot of great reviews.
Great food, amazing service

This place is a hidden gym in Lakeview.  My GF and I are regulars here now and it's become one of my favorite low key places to eat in the city.  The menu is awesome and the Cuban Spiced Won Tons are the perfect start to your meal and the quesadilla is also a home run. All of the burgers are really well down with the right amount of creativity without being too much. They have a rotating list of cool martinis and they are delicious and always have plenty of booze.  The servers are great and the owner, Alex, is such a friendly and hard working guy.  I cannot recommend this place enough.  Great patio for the summers also!

In my opinion this is the best place of its kind in the city. The staff is excellent and knows you very quickly. It’s rarely crowded on week days but gets bumpin on the weekends. The food is fantastic and the drinks are moreso. Check this place out and get the Artichoke dip with a Moscow mule.
Great service, good food.
Service and Food are amazing!!
Amazing sandwiches and a good selection of craft beer. 👍🏻
Great Food. Been here for work all week and been ordering food from here every day. It's that great.
Very pleasant place to spend some time...

GET THE SHRIMP TACOS! Jason was a fantastic bartender, and the vibe was excellent. 20’s-30s crowd. Great sit down place to have some drinks, while actually being able to hear the person next to you! A hidden gem.
Just amazing food. Interesting spins on classic bar food.
Very friendly staff, great server. Nice ambience and overall tasty food and nice drink choice for a tavern & grill!
Very quaint space. Friendly and attentive staff. Food was delicious. Looking forward to visiting when the patio is open.

Our favorite neighborhood bar/restaurant--for both summer (great patio) and winter. Everything is surprisingly excellent for what looks like a neighborhood bar from the outside more than a high quality restaurant--craft cocktails with homemade ginger beer, and great food--from burgers to the 'real' entrees like steak and salmon. And the staff are awesome--always friendly, fun, and clearly invested in the place. Worth becoming a regular.
The burger was good! So was the service.
Great selection of craft beer, exceptional food and service. A must come again!
Awesome experience here again. Staff is ultra friendly and attentive. The food was outstanding as well. I had the wings and also shrimp tacos.
The Monday burger deal is great! Tap beer was on special and priced great, even the craft brews.

The outdoor patio is a nice place to grab a drink. We had a good experience there on Saturday night, although the waitress accidentally spilled some of one of our drinks (about 1/4). She apologized, but she could have gone a bit further by offering us a discount or a free complementary drink. No major complaints. We still liked our experience there. But, I would not give the service a 5 out of 5.
Great food, amazing service, and a relaxing patio.
Just a small place with great seafood. Absolutely impressed
Alex & Jason made our business trip to Chicago a great experience.  Service was spot on! Food was delicious! Definitely will be a "Must" the next time we are in Chi-Town.
Delicious drinks, friendly staff, and nice mood.
Very nice!   Excellent burgers, tacos and salad.   Def recommend.
We tried to go to Kumas Too but their kitchen was closed so we walked down to Matisse since they serve food late and had a great time. Great service and great food. I recommend it.
Great customer service, good food.  Late night kitchen is a plus.!

Do you see this sandwich? You must get this sandwich. Bistro steak is a high quality steak dinner in an affordable sandwich. According to my boyfriend whose plate was blessed to have this creation: "The Bistro steak is like the Mariana Trench. You keep going deeper as you chew, expecting to hit the gristly bottom of every steak you've ever had. Bracing for that flavorless, yet pleseant, texture signaling the end of your bite. Instead it just goes deeper. The umami of the mushrooms, spinach, aioli and cheese overlapped to create a seemingly infinite sea of umami."  Also, the Buffalo sandwich is great and the staff is fabulous.
I love this place. Nicest staff in Lakeview, fantastic burgers. Try the baked brie.
Stopped in here for a late night bite and beer, and was pleasantly surprised. Food was great, beer was cold, prices were fair, and Arthur was running things perfcperf. Hit them up!
Always delicious!!
Decent food and clean place.
Relaxed and dimly lit setting. Good daily specials. Delicious cocktail specials. Friendly staff
Great food and great service. Alex is the best!
Great Food and drinks! Fun atmosphere

Five stars because of the service. I enjoyed the cozy atmosphere, although there was some feeling that it might have been a bit crowded. The food was great and although I didn't have the drinks the prices were OK.

This place was awesome. We were staying at a hotel down the block and as we walked by the place we checked out their outside menu. Decided to stop in. It was amazing. The atmosphere was quaint, the service was spot on and the food was amazing!   It was so good we went back for dinner the next day. If this place was in the Milwaukee area where we lived we would be there once a week. We will definitely come back when we are in Chicago again!!
Good food, good drinks, good service. Quaint bar below street level. Try the baked brie.

Found this spot about 3 years ago and was hooked then went back and the quality of food and service is still excellent. Alex is a gracious host and one of the best servers there! But all servers we're beyond friendly really complete the experience

First time in this establishment and i had an amazing time. The atmosphere is lively, very cozy. I tried their Moscow Mule and Masterpiece burger and I can tell you I was more than happy with my choice. Service was on point, overall a great experience.
Great drinks and fun people
Best burger in town
Wonderful place to hang around.
For sure my new favorite bar in this area so far!  Staff was really friendly and the bartender was very knowledgeable.  I had the chicken pear panini sandwich and it was very good!!  I will be back.

Stumbled upon this place while walking and was lured in by one of my favorite MGMT songs playing.  My martini was delicious, the food we both had was amazing! The pretzel buns rock! Our server Kristina and the other staff were on point and friendly.  This made our night,  thank you Matisse!
Is amazing

Stumbled here on accident, but the food was delicious! Black bean burger was great, sweet potato fries were yummy, and even the salad was good AND I HATE SALAD BUT IT'S GOOD FOR MY BODY. Highly recommended! Came in on a Wednesday so $24 dollar bottle of wine special going on.
Everything about this place feels right. The environment, the aesthetic, the service, it's all stellar!
Just happened to be shopping in the neighborhood when we came across this bar. Great beer selection and Arthur took care of us while we were there!

Great bar with truly awesome staff and very reasonable drink prices. Some if the food is fantastic too, but I'll be the first to say, not all of it. They have a really amazing patio upstairs and their indoor area downstairs has a pretty good feel too it too. Their taco Tuesday special is pretty good. $7 for three generous tacos and salsas, $4 margaritas. Everything was delicious and service was wonderful!
One of my favorite places in Lakeview. Great service, drinks and food. Try the baked brie appetizer, amazing.

Kristina is a dream come true. I've never had a better server in my life. Her laugh is contagious...i hope she doesn't get fired for this. AAAANNNNNNDDDD the food is dank and the bathroom is sweet. Cheers.

There's a decent beer selection here and food is OK, though I've never been wowed by it. My favorite part about this place is their ambiance: quite dark and moody but obviously modern and fresh. Certainly not a bad establishment to spend a couple hours on a rainy day or an afternoon that got too hot and humid outside.
Ate outside, everything was great!
Good food and prices.
Great Bartender and service Staff. Food was fantastic!
The best service and freshest beef tenderloin. Wonderful sweet potatoes fries...yummy
The food is fresh and spectacular. So is the bartender. EXCELLENT music. Very clean. The staff is so friendly and nice. We will be back!
Excellent service, drinks, and food! Went with a large-ish group and they were very accommodating. Meal and appetizers came out quick and fresh. Everything tasted good as well.

Matisse is one of my favorite bars in Lakeview.  Why?  Because it doesn't have a gimmick.  It doesn't cater to only one subset of the population.  It doesn't overcharge.  It's not loud or jam-packed with people.  It's a bar done right, and the patio seating is just the cherry on top.  Service is good inside and out, even on St. Patrick's Day!  Now that's an accomplishment.  Located between the DePaul college bars and the Wrigleyville vortex, Matisse is in the perfect location to be your chill neighborhood spot.
If you don't go in for their specials your missing out. Arthur and Ian are both great bartenders as well!!
Good food, friendly staff.

Great neighborhood bar. Good drinks and the best staff. Bartenders to wait staff to kitchen everybody is friendly and helpful. We are in town every few months and usually stop in for a drink or two during out trip...the staff remembers us wether it has been 3 or 6 months since we were last in. Really worth a trip for the food drinks and most importantly the wonderful staff.
Amazingly high quality food for very reasonable price. Nice new interior and friendly staff. Cool environment, good music.
Great place. Great specials. Friendly staff.
Love this place. Photos don't do it justice. Really well designed.
Fun place for a few drinks. Outside seating.

After being invited to come in by the friendly waitstaff, I was pleasantly surprised by the offerings. First off, a great selection of craft beers and drinks. Our waitress enlightened us to the Moscow Mule which is made with their home-made gingerbeer, this is a must try. They offer a great selection of burgers with a flavor for everyone (I had a spicy burger with ghost pepper cheddar and roasted habanero pepers, which was the perfect amount of kick). Burgers are served wirh pretzel buns which is a nice touch.  Overall, great little spot with a nice assortment of drinks, good food, a very friendly waitstaff, all at a good price. I wasnt planning to go to this restaurant initially, but was pleasanlty surprised by food and service. Check em out.
This is the place to be at!! Alex awesome 😀 the new look is modern,the food is finger licking good,the ambiance is great!! My favorite place to eat!!!&&& Great service
Great food when drunk (since everything is closed) and great bartenders who are lovely. The whole place is awesome and hidden under ground, like Narnia.
Great food for when you're drunk!
I love this place! Went here after I turned 21 and the food was just as great as the atmosphere. But nothing can beat those great deals!!!

The servers are the best part. Some have been there for years and really know their stuff. Surprising beer menu that gave me a chance to try new things. The patio is open to well-behaved dogs. If you can, head out to the patio; the inside of the restaurant isn't bad, but it's basement level and kinda dark.

Love this place! Food is really good and reasonably priced (they also have a late night menu!). Atmosphere is chill, staff is really friendly and they have daily drink specials and homemade ginger beer.
Terry the bartender is amazing. Forget who ever was saying the music is bad, I love it.

Who doesn't enjoy to be in a friendly environment? Well, if you need some time to relax meanwhile you're having your favorite drink, this is the place you could do it. Btw, their sweet potato fries are outstanding!
ok, no big deal
Awesome food. Great Drinks! Amazing service!

By far my favorite bar. The atmosphere is always lively. The food good, don't skip on the soup or meat balls. Friendly staff who knows what they are doing, making sure the customers are taken care of, and food coming out fast Don't miss this amazing bar.

In town for a concert at the Riviera, close to our hotel, loved the food (steak nachos, shrimp tacos!), our bartender was OUTSTANDING, I feel bad for not catching his name, but I will always remember that experience. Highly recommend.
I love Matisse. The food is far better than average bar food. The shrimp tacos are the best. And half-priced wine night on Wednesdays is my favorite!
Great little place. Good food and good drinks! Worth the stop if in the area!

$5 martinis on Fridays. Matisse, out.  Honestly, is there anything else you need to know! Their is a long list of fabulous flavors, one of my favorites is key lime.  Okay, yes they also have a Photo Hunt machine at the bar. It plays other games as well but Photo hunt is the best.  Matisse has a cozy interior and a great patio with great people watching on Diversey.  If you are still not sold, their food as way above average bar fare.  I've been coming here for 8 years and never not had a great time!

My favorite place to go on Tuesday nights in the summer! They have specials EVERY night of the week but their cheap sangria and taco platters on Tuesdays bring me back again and again and again.  Large pitchers of sangria (red or white) are just $12 and delicious shrimp taco plates are just $6. Plus you've got a great patio and excellent, excellent service! Seriously go but plan on getting there before 7pm or the patio will fill up.
username: NowYouKnow Events, Chicago's Best Event Calendar

caption: Love it! Always great food and drinks. Have tried their nachos, burgers, and mac-n-cheese, chocolate martinis and they are all amazing! The waiter who's name is I believe Alex is very friendly and attentive. The wonderful environment to sit back or play board games before/after your food
One of my favorite finds this trip.  Excellent food and drinks at a very reasonable price.

The best part about Matisse is the sangria.  It is the best deal in Lincoln Park with $10 a pitcher for their medium sized sangria.  The food is good bar type food, perfect to split with friends.  The bartenders and waiters are really friendly and make the experience overall a good one.

Visiting this bar was a result of random walking.  A friend and I went here after we freeloaded the Borders near-by of their books and WiFi when it closed at midnight.  We were just walking until she pulled me into this bar.  We just wanted some time to talk since her apartment is possibly contaminated with the flu/cough spit/piggy aids.  This bar felt cool the minute we walked in.  It's your normal L-shaped bar with barstool tables and some couch space.  The music was not too loud, the waitress was very attentive and bingo! - Connect Four!  They had a a couple games to play with in the back and we were playing Connect Four like it was our job.  I got beat in every game, but who cares - imported beer was $5 a glass.  When we got our check - we were expecting $20.  Nope! $10!  We stumbled in on a half price night!  All drinks are half-price on Thursdays!
Delicious food! average service,
